        {
          "user": "sudonhim",
          "content": [
            {
              "text": "LC claims that the current leaders lack the moral authority to sacrifice their children, such authority can come only from god.",
              "kind": "text"
            }
          ],
          "id": "1"
        }
      ],
      "newAnchor": "28"
    },
    {
      "anchor": "p7.l1",
      "annotations": [
        {
          "user": "sudonhim",
          "content": [
            {
              "text": "Rebuking the US government for drafting soliders into Vietnam made you popular with the radical left, and thus now Cohen turns on the communists to rebuke them also. A decade later in a live performances of Diamonds in the Mine LC refers back to this song. He sings \"I thought I told you all about it / back in days of Vietnam / when your poets marched for Uncle Ho / and your jocks for Uncle Sam / well whose side are you on today / whose song are you gonna sing / with the mega stench of corpses / that is blowing in the wind!\"",
              "kind": "text"
            }
          ],
          "id": "1"
        }
      ],
      "newAnchor": "37"
    },
    {
      "anchor": "p7.l3",
      "annotations": [
        {
          "user": "sudonhim",
          "content": [
            {
              "text": "This is a deep critique of communism. If men are to be brothers - brothers according to whose plan? Communists reject that it was according to God's plan, but struggle to agree on an alternative.",
              "kind": "text"
            }
          ],
          "id": "1"
        }
      ],
      "newAnchor": "39"
